- "danced on the hardwood" is a metaphor for playing basketball games;
- "watchful eye of Scott Foster" refers to the games officiated by the referee Scott Foster;
- "captained" in this context refers to the player's participation in the game.

- 'leading players' refers to players who have the highest scores;
- 'top 5' implies the top 5 players based on their final scores within each team;
- 'contributed to their teams' victories' means the final score was greater than zero;
- 'focusing on the top achievers' implies using the ranking of scores within each team to determine the top players.

sql:
SELECT t.team_name
FROM teams t
JOIN game_statistics gs ON t.team_id = gs.team_id
WHERE gs.quarter1_score = (
    SELECT MAX(quarter1_score) FROM game_statistics
);

SELECT overtime_score
FROM game_statistics
WHERE overtime_score > 0;

SELECT game_id
FROM game_statistics
WHERE final_score = (
  SELECT MAX(final_score)
  FROM game_statistics
);

SELECT player_name, jersey_number
FROM players
WHERE team_id = (SELECT team_id FROM players WHERE player_id = 1);

